b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29102.htm)  [Next](sbe29104.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KA _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 4.\n\n1 4_1. During the northern course of the sun, in the time of the increasing\nmoon, under an auspicious Nakshatra the tonsure (of the child's head), the\ninitiation (of a Brahma _k_ arin), the cutting of the beard, and marriage\n(should be celebrated).\n\n2\\. According to some (teachers), marriage (may be celebrated) at any time.\n\n3\\. Before those (ceremonies) let him sacrifice four \xc3\x82 _g_ ya oblations\xc2\x97\n\n4\\. With the three (verses), 'Agni, thou purifiest life' (Rig-veda I X, 66, 10\nseq.), and with (the one verse), 'Pra _g_ apati, no other one than thou' (Rig-\nVeda X, 121, 10).\n\n5 5. Or with the Vyah _ri_ tis.\n\n6 6. According to some (teachers), the one and the other.\n\n7 7. No such(oblations), according to some (teachers).\n\n8\\. At the marriage the fourth oblation with the verse, 'Thou (O Agni) art\nAryaman towards the girls' (Rig-veda V, 3, 2).\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[164:4_1](sbe29103.htm#fr_374) 4, 1. Sa\xe1\xb9\x85kh.-G _ri_ hya I, 5, 2-5.\n\n[164:5](sbe29103.htm#fr_375) With the words, bhu _h_ , bhuva _h_ , sva _h_ ,\nand with the three words together.\n\n[164:6](sbe29103.htm#fr_376) Thus eight oblations are offered, four with the\nfour _Ri_ _k_ as quoted in the fourth Sutra, and four with the Vyah _ri_ tis.\n\n[164:7](sbe29103.htm#fr_377) Neither the oblations with the _Ri_ _k_ as nor\nthose with the Vyah _ri_ tis.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 5](sbe29104.htm)\n\n"